title: Men I'm Not Married To (Version 2)
description:
Dorothy Parker was a poet, writer and satirist of the foibles of the early 20th century (not least, of Prohibition), and a founding member of New York’s Algonquin Round Table, a group of prominent artistic and social critics, actors and wits.

This is a short collection of humorously critical descriptions of various men on the periphery of her “inner circle,” which explain why they are men she is not married to. - Summary by Kirsten Wever
